tails, small plates, and some of the best views in the city. The bar features both indoor and outdoor seating, with heat lamps and blankets provided during cooler months. For convenience, we offer 24-hour room service with an extensive menu, and our grab-and-go market in the lobby provides fresh salads, sandwiches, and Stumptown coffee for guests on the move.\n\nThe hotel\'s wellness facilities help you maintain your routine while traveling, with a 24-hour fitness center featuring Peloton bikes, free weights, and cardio equipment with personal entertainment screens. We offer complimentary yoga mats in every suite and can arrange private training sessions or in-suite yoga classes. While we don\'t have a spa on-site, our concierge has partnerships with nearby luxury spas and can arrange treatments with preferred rates. The rooftop also features a seasonal outdoor area perfect for morning meditation or evening relaxation. For business travelers, our business center offers private workstations, printing services, and meeting rooms equipped with video conferencing technology.\n\nMetropolitan Suites\' location is truly unbeatable for exploring New York City. Step outside and you\'re within walking distance of iconic landmarks including Rockefeller Center, the Museum of Modern Art, Carnegie Hall, and Central Park. Times Square and Broadway theaters are just three blocks away, making it easy to catch a show. The hotel is surrounded by flagship stores of luxury brands and department stores like Saks Fifth Avenue and Bergdorf Goodman. Multiple subway lines are within two blocks, providing easy access to all five boroughs. Our concierge team, many of whom are native New Yorkers, can secure reservations at the city\'s hottest restaurants, arrange private tours of museums, or get you tickets to sold-out shows. With valet parking, a business center, and meeting spaces available, Metropolitan Suites caters to every type of traveler seeking an authentic New York experience with style and comfort.',
